race.comment: MACCBI (1) has been around the mark in stronger maidens and gets his best chance yet to shed the tag. Freshened since late August and tuned up with a tidy Randwick trial, he maps to get every possible and will take holding out if he brings his best. MAMMA MIA (12) made up strong ground on debut and should appreciate the low draw. Big improver. LA NINA (5) also took a nice step forward second-up where she was ridden more quietly than on debut to run on into a placing. Has genuine top-three claims. Connections have been patient with UNNATURAL POWER (6) who debuts as a five-year-old. Trials have been encouraging enough.
